summary: This is an FBI Electronic Communication documenting the submission of returns from administrative subpoenas to the case file for the Jeffrey Epstein investigation. The subpoenas targeted birth records and subscriber/toll information from multiple telecommunications companies.

persons.name: Jeffrey Epstein
persons.context: The document is an FBI communication regarding the submission of administrative subpoena returns to his case file, indicating an active investigation into him.

events.title: Full Investigation Initiated
events.description: The FBI formally initiated a full investigation into Jeffrey Epstein.

events.title: Submission of Subpoena Returns
events.description: FBI agent submits returns from administrative subpoenas (for birth certificates and telecom records) to the Epstein case file.

keyFacts: The FBI initiated a full investigation into Jeffrey Epstein on July 25, 2006.
As of July 12, 2013, the investigation was active, with agents submitting new administrative subpoena returns to the case file.
Subpoenas were issued to the Palm Beach County Health Department for a birth certificate (the subject's name is redacted).
Subpoenas were issued to major telecommunications providers (Metro PCS, Bell South, AT&T, T-Mobile) for subscriber and toll information.
The document is an internal FBI administrative record (FD-1057 Electronic Communication) used to formally add evidence to the case file.
